description:
Implement the budget truncation logic that runs AFTER rendering. Budgets truncate deterministically - they do NOT error.

Location: crates/baml-bridge/src/prompt/world.rs

```rust
impl PromptWorld {
    /// Apply max_total_chars budget truncation
    /// NOTE: This is NOT an error - truncation is valid output
    fn apply_budget_truncation(&self, output: RenderOutput, pv: &PromptValue) -> RenderOutput {
        let max = pv.session.settings.max_total_chars;

        if output.text.len() <= max {
            return output;
        }

        // Truncate to budget, leaving room for suffix
        let suffix = '... (truncated)';
        let truncate_at = max.saturating_sub(suffix.len());

        // Find valid char boundary
        let mut end = truncate_at;
        while end > 0 && !output.text.is_char_boundary(end) {
            end -= 1;
        }

        let mut text = output.text[..end].to_string();
        text.push_str(suffix);

        RenderOutput { text }
    }
}
```

Key invariant: truncation is NOT an error. The spec is explicit:
- 'Budgets always truncate deterministically - truncation is NOT an error'
- 'Only renderer/template failures are errors'

This makes the system predictable - you always get output, and it's always within budget.
